        "title": "feat(control-ui): render Mermaid code fences in webchat",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Render fenced ` ```mermaid ` blocks in Control UI webchat with lazy-loaded Mermaid and dedicated chat styling.\n- Keep Mermaid source blocks collapsible and copy-friendly in the transcript UI.\n- Harden Mermaid rendering:\n  - case-insensitive language fence detection (`mermaid` / `Mermaid`)\n  - sanitize rendered SVG before insertion\n  - guard against transient module-load/render failures\n\n## Screenshots\nRendered Mermaid diagram in Control UI webchat:\n\n![Mermaid diagram rendered in Control UI webchat](https://files.catbox.moe/efp3l7.png)\n\n## CI/compat follow-ups included in this PR\n- Stabilize channel contract tests by moving some imports from module scope into test scope to avoid eager side effects.\n- Update contract registry imports to use explicit extension internals where runtime APIs no longer expose these helpers.\n- Make bundle MCP path assertions robust across symlink/realpath environments (Windows/CI path normalization).\n\n## Files touched\n- UI Mermaid integration:\n  - `ui/src/ui/markdown.ts`\n  - `ui/src/ui/markdown.test.ts`\n  - `ui/src/ui/mermaid.ts`\n  - `ui/src/styles/chat.css`\n  - `ui/src/styles/chat/mermaid.css`\n  - `ui/src/ui/app-lifecycle.ts`\n  - `ui/package.json`\n- Contract/CI stabilization:\n  - `src/channels/plugins/contracts/inbound.contract.test.ts`\n  - `src/channels/plugins/contracts/registry.ts`\n  - `src/plugins/bundle-mcp.test.ts`\n  - `pnpm-lock.yaml`\n\n## Test plan\n- Unit tests: markdown rendering tests updated for Mermaid behavior and failure handling.\n- Contract tests: inbound/registry contract paths updated for current plugin boundaries.\n- CI: full repository checks.\n",
